.TH "drm_display_info_set_bus_formats" 9 "drm_display_info_set_bus_formats" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_display_info_set_bus_formats \- set the supported bus formats
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drm_display_info_set_bus_formats
.BI "(struct drm_display_info *info "  ","
.BI "const u32 *formats "  ","
.BI "unsigned int num_formats "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "info" 12
display info to store bus formats in
.IP "formats" 12
array containing the supported bus formats
.IP "num_formats" 12
the number of entries in the fmts array
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Store the supported bus formats in display info structure.
See MEDIA_BUS_FMT_* definitions in include/uapi/linux/media-bus-format.h for
a full list of available formats.
